Integrating agent readiness into Cloudflare URL Scanner 




 Cloudflare's URL Scanner lets you submit any URL and get a detailed report on it: HTTP headers, TLS certificates, DNS records, technologies used, performance data, and security signals.

Think of it as a sitemap written for an LLM to read rather than a crawler to index:

 # My Site
> A developer platform for building on the edge.
## Documentation
- [Getting Started](https://example.com/docs/start.md)
- [API Reference](https://example.com/docs/api.md)
## Changelog
- [Release Notes](https://example.com/changelog.md) 
 Markdown content negotiation goes even further.

Unlike links buried inside HTML, the Link header is part of the HTTP response itself, which means an agent can find links to resources without having to parse any markup:

 HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Link: </.well-known/api-catalog>; rel="api-catalog" 


